  "title": "Hydraulic Engineer",
  "description": "<ul><li>Design, develop, and maintain hydraulic systems and\n     components used in machinery, marine equipment, and industrial\n     applications.</li><li>Conduct troubleshooting, fault diagnostics, and\n     repair of hydraulic pumps, motors, cylinders, valves, hoses, and control\n     systems.</li><li>Perform installation, testing, flushing, and\n     commissioning of hydraulic systems onboard vessels, offshore platforms, or\n     industrial sites.</li><li>Prepare technical drawings, schematics, and hydraulic\n     circuit diagrams.</li><li>Carry out pressure testing, flow checks, and\n     performance analysis to ensure optimal system operation.</li><li>Conduct preventive and corrective maintenance on\n     hydraulic equipment and machinery.</li><li>Collaborate with mechanical, electrical, and project\n     teams during repair, modification, and upgrade works.</li><li>Evaluate damaged hydraulic components and recommend\n     repair procedures or replacements.</li><li>Ensure compliance with safety standards, marine\n     regulations, and industry best practices during all hydraulic operations.</li><li>Assist in preparing quotations, job scope\n     descriptions, cost estimates, and material lists.</li><li>Prepare service reports, inspection reports, and\n     documentation for completed works.</li><li>Support procurement by identifying suitable hydraulic\n     parts, seals, hoses, fittings, and consumables.</li><li>Provide technical advice and solutions to customers\n     and internal teams.</li><li>Participate in root cause analysis (RCA) for\n     recurring hydraulic failures and propose preventive actions.</li></ul>",
